summary: RV bypass with TO1 coexistence retry behavior
description: |
    Tests RV bypass with multiple unreachable owner URLs falling back
    to normal TO1 on the second directive:
    - RV bypass enabled with unreachable owners triggers TO2 failures
    - Default TO2 retry delay (0s) means no delay between attempts
    - Fallback to normal TO1 when bypass fails
    - Directive delay applied between directives

test: ./test-retry-rv-bypass-to1-coexistence.sh

framework: shell

duration: 10m

require:
  - go-fdo-server
  - go-fdo-server-manufacturer
  - go-fdo-server-owner
  - go-fdo-server-rendezvous

tag:
  - fdo
  - e2e
  - protocol
  - retry
  - rv-bypass
  - rpm
  - server
